        "created_at": "2024-07-08T17:31:06.636Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Around 2022, Signal introduced the concept of “Signal Connections”. (I will use capitals, so it is obvious I am referring to this concept.) Based on the date of the <a href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20221109142401/https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/articles/5008009166234-Stories#story_connections\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">first Wayback Machine capture</a> of the <a href=\"https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/search?utf8=%E2%9C%93&amp;query=%22signal+connections%22\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">only</a> Support page that mentions Connections, this was probably introduced with the <a href=\"https://signal.org/blog/introducing-stories/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Stories feature</a>.</p>\n<p>According to the above Help page, one’s Signal Connections are the Signal users that fulfill any of these three:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>“Everyone in your phone’s contact list who uses Signal.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>“Anyone you’ve had a 1:1 conversation with in Signal even if you haven’t added them as a contact.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>“Anyone whose message request you’ve accepted in Signal.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The same Help page describes that a list of Signal Connections can be viewed (only on the phone app) in Settings - Stories - My Story - View (next to All Signal connections).</p>\n<p>This list seems to be the same as the list of users that appears when I press the New message button of the Signal phone app. However, it is not the same on my desktop app.</p>\n<p>There are many contacts that I used to have in my phone’s contact book. My phone’s contacts are synced with Signal, so these contacts used to appear in my Signal phone app and desktop app too. I have never exchanged a message with them and neither of us has sent a message request. After I deleted them from my phone’s contact book, they disappeared from the list that appears when I press New message on my Signal phone app. They no longer appear in Settings - Stories - My Story - View either.</p>\n<p>However, they do appear in the list when press New message on the Signal <em>desktop</em> app, and also if I search for their names in the Chats bar. (Interestingly, it is not consistent. Not <em>all</em> of those deleted contacts appear, some actually did disappear.) If I click on their names, they appear as new empty chats on the top of my Chats, even though I didn’t send or request anything. And, the strangest of all things, if I go into such a chat and click on the name (at the beginning of the chat where they have an arrow “&gt;” after the name), Signal tells me they are still my system contact and that they are my Signal Connection too!</p>\n<p>My questions:</p>\n<p><strong>1. Are these “Limbo Connections” part of my real Signal Connections or not?</strong></p>\n<p><strong>2. What privileges do these “Limbo Connections” have over users who have never been in my phone’s address book or my Signal contact list?</strong></p>\n<p><strong>3. Could there be further Connections (“Limbo” or otherwise) that aren’t visible in either Signal app?</strong></p>\n<p><strong>4. How can I revoke the privileges of “Limbo Connections” without blocking them?</strong> Blocking every one of them would be unfeasible (there are way too many) and I don’t want to have a record of them in any of my apps. I want them to be like strangers who can only see, and have to go through, the same as someone who is not a real Signal Connection.</p>",
