        "cooked": "<p>Great write-up! I’m wondering if the current behavior is desirable. I have many stale Signal Connections and no easy way to remove them. They are not in my contacts, the conversations have been deleted, but they persist. Unblocking a contact returns them do your connections, which is unpleasant. It seems like signal is missing a way to remove connections. It can always re-add them based on the same criteria</p>",
